{"id":"256496482_Role_of_Edge_Atoms_in_the_Hysteretic_Behaviour_of_3D_Spin_Crossover_Nanoparticles_Revealed_by_an_Ising-Like_Model","abstract":"We have applied a phenomenological two-level Ising-like model to study the case of 3D coordination polymers showing strongly cooperative but incomplete spin-transition behaviour. Our numerical results focus on nanoparticles of the cyanide-bridged 3D network Fe(pyrazine)[Pt(CN)(4)], considering several factors (i.e. temperature, pressure), the role of short- and long-range interactions and the system size. To be consistent with the experimental studies on a nanometric scale, we used a semiexact method (Monte Carlo entropic sampling) to solve a system that contains molecules on each surface in the high-spin state (edge atoms). A preliminary analysis of the short-range antiferromagnetic case has been carried out to illustrate the three-step transition case.","authors":["Daniel Chiruta","Jorge Linares","Mihai Dimian","Yasser Alayli"],"meta":["October 2013Berichte der deutschen chemischen Gesellschaft 2013(29):n/a-n/a","DOI:10.1002/ejic.201300757","Project: Spin crossover materials"],"references":["254861078_Monte_Carlo_entropic_sampling_applied_to_spin_crossover_solids_The_squareness_of_the_thermal_hysteresis_loop","254257920_Analysis_of_long-range_interaction_effects_on_phase_transitions_in_two-step_spin-crossover_chains_by_using_Ising-type_systems_and_Monte_Carlo_entropic_sampling_technique","253924919_Study_of_the_relaxation_in_diluted_spin_crossover_molecular_magnets_in_the_framework_of_the_mechano-elastic_model","244296558_Monte_Carlo_simulations_for_1-_and_2D_spin_crossover_compounds_using_the_atom-phonon_coupling_model","243457324_Ising-like_model_for_the_two-step_spin-crossover","243457302_Analytical_solution_of_1D_Ising-like_systems_modified_by_weak_long_range_interaction_Application_to_spin_crossover_compounds","243426932_Two-dimensional_Ising-like_model_with_specific_edge_effects_for_spin-crossover_nanoparticles_A_Mon